What is an ElevatedButton?
Simple definition: A button that appears to "float" above the screen with a shadow underneath it. It's the most common button in Material Design apps.

Think of it like: A raised button with a shadow, like the "Submit" or "Login" buttons you see in most apps.

========================================Visual Difference =========================================================
[Button Type]	          [Look]	                                    [When to Use]
ElevatedButton          Has shadow, "floats" above background	       Important actions (Submit, Login, Save)
TextButton	            Just text, no background	                   Less important actions (Cancel, Learn More)
OutlinedButton	        Has border, no shadow	                       Medium importance (Secondary actions)
IconButton	            Just an icon	                               Toolbar actions (Search, Settings)
